                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Japan boost to sewerage revamp bid
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Chief minister Naveen Pattnaik lays the foundation stone of the integrated sewerage system in Bhubaneswar. Picture by Sanjib Mukherjee                                  
	Bhubaneswar, July 15: The capital city is all set to get an integrated sewerage system by 2011. The estimated cost of the project is Rs 754.23 crore.         
	The project would be taken up with an additional central assistance of Rs 399.13 crore under the Jawaharlal Nehru Urban Renewal Mission, loan assistance of Rs 99.78 crore from Japan Bank for International Co-operation and Rs 140 crore from the 12th Finance Commission Grant.         
	The project has been designed to cater to the needs of a projected population of 22 lakh by 2041, covering an area of 145sqkm in Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation limits and fringe areas.         
	The Union government has signed a loan agreement for the project, which will be available with 0.75 per cent rate of interest, payable over 40 years with 10 years of moratorium period.         
	A detailed project report, prepared with the technical assistance from IIT, Roorkee, received its final nod from the funding agencies and the foundation stone of the project was laid by chief minister Naveen Patnaik today.         
	The project includes laying of 412km underground gravity sewerage system in uncovered areas, replacement and renovation of all existing sewers, construction of 34 pumping stations and six sewerage treatment plants and construction of low-cost sanitation units.                                                                                                                                                                          
